🚀 CI/CD Pipeline using Jenkins, SonarQube, Docker, Kubernetes & ArgoCD

📌 Overview

This project implements an end-to-end CI/CD pipeline for a Java Spring Boot application using:

Jenkins
SonarQube
Docker
Docker Hub
Kubernetes
Argo CD

🔁 CI/CD Flow

Developer → GitHub → Jenkins → SonarQube → Build Jar → create Docker image → push to Docker Hub → Git Update manifest files using (sh) → ArgoCD detects changes →  automatically deployes on Kubernetes Cluster → Application run's
 
⚙️ Pipeline Stages 
1 Code Commit 
Developer pushes code to GitHub repository. 
Jenkins pipeline is triggered. 

2 SonarQube Analysis 
Runs code quality scan using Maven. 
Checks: 
  Bugs 
  Vulnerabilities 
  Code Smells 
  Quality Gate must pass

3 Build Application
Maven builds the Spring Boot JAR file

mvn clean package -DskipTests

4 Verify Build
Confirms JAR file exists in target/ directory.


5 Generate Image Tag
Unique tag created using:
BUILD_NUMBER + GIT_COMMIT_ID

6 Docker Build
Builds Docker image with generated tag.
docker build -t sonyragam/java-backend-app:<TAG> 

7 Docker Push
Pushes image to Docker Hub.
docker push sonyragam/java-backend-app:<TAG>

8 pdate Kubernetes Manifest
Updates image tag in deployment YAML.
sed -i "s|image:.*|image: sonyragam/java-backend-app:<TAG>|" K8s/deployment.yml

9 Git Push (GitOps Step)
Commits updated deployment file.
Pushes changes to GitHub.

10 ArgoCD Sync
ArgoCD detects Git changes automatically.
Syncs updated configuration to Kubernetes.

11 Kubernetes Deployment
New pods are created with updated image.
Service exposes application via NodePort.

12 Application Access
http://localhost:30007

📊 Output
✅ SonarQube Quality Gate: PASSED
✅ Jenkins Build: SUCCESS
✅ Docker Image: PUSHED
✅ ArgoCD: SYNCED & HEALTHY
✅ Kubernetes: RUNNING


🎯 Key Features
End-to-End CI/CD Automation
Code Quality Integration
Dynamic Docker Image Tagging
GitOps-based Deployment
Automated Kubernetes Rollout

🧠 Workflow Summary
Code pushed to GitHub
Jenkins runs pipeline
SonarQube validates code
Maven builds application
Docker image created & pushed
Deployment YAML updated
Changes pushed to GitHub
ArgoCD deploys to Kubernetes
Application goes live
